🥥 did you know?
   ├─ path contains \`[\` which is a glob character
   ├─ to treat \`[\` as literal, use either:
   │  ├─ --literal flag: rhx cpsafe --literal './doc.[ref].md' './dest.md'
   │  └─ escape syntax: rhx cpsafe './doc.\\[ref\\].md' ...
   └─ see: rhx cpsafe --help
"
`;

